X=df.drop(["Attrition"],axis=1)
y=df["Attrition"]
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

X_train,X_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(X,y,test_size=0.2,random_state=0)

from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression

lr=LogisticRegression()
lr.fit(X_train,y_train)
lrpred=lr.predict(X_test)
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score,classification_report

print(f"ACCURACY = {accuracy_score(y_test,lrpred)} ")
print(classification_report(y_test,lrpred))
probability=lr.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
fpr,tpr,threshsholds = roc_curve(y_test,probability)
plt.plot(fpr,tpr)
plt.xlabel('FPR')
plt.ylabel('TPR')
plt.title('ROC CURVE')
plt.show()

from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier

maxa=-1e8

    dtc=DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=i)
    dtc.fit(X_train,y_train)

    if maxa<k:
        maxa=k

from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV

 'criterion':['gini','entropy'],
  'splitter':['best','random'],
  'max_depth':[1,2,3,4,5],
  'max_features':['auto', 'sqrt', 'log2']
    
}

df=pd.read_csv("WA_Fn-UseC_-HR-Employee-Attrition.csv")
df.head()
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder

cc=df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns
le=LabelEncoder()

for i in cc:
    df[i]=le.fit_transform(df[i])
df.head()
# REMOVING ONLY SOME OUTLIERS

oc2=["MonthlyIncome","TotalWorkingYears","YearsAtCompany"]
oc2

for i in oc2:
    iqr = df[i].quantile(0.75) - df[i].quantile(0.25)
    lower_threshold = df[i].quantile(0.25) - 1.5 * iqr
    upper_threshold = df[i].quantile(0.75) + 1.5 * iqr
    df = df[ (df[i] >lower_threshold) & (df[i] <upper_threshold)]
